# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Marketing Plugin — Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Then run /marketing:setup in Claude Code to configure the rest.
# See SETUP.md for step-by-step instructions on getting each credential.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env to git — it contains your private API keys.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── Meta Ads MCP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Reads campaign data, creates campaigns, uploads creatives,
#               manages ad sets, budgets, and performance reporting.
#
# No API key needed — Meta Ads uses OAuth via the MCP connection.
# Add the Meta Ads MCP to your Claude Code settings:
#
#   "mcpServers": {
#     "meta-ads": { "url": "https://mcp.facebook.com/ads" }
#   }
#
# Then connect your Meta Business account through the OAuth prompt.
# The MCP handles authentication, token refresh, and rate limiting automatically.
#
# Note: Your Meta ad account ID is configured in config.yaml (not here).

# ─── Cloudflare ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Deploys landing pages to Cloudflare Pages and runs lead
#               capture webhooks via Cloudflare Workers.
#
# How to get your API token:
#   1. Go to dash.cloudflare.com → Profile (top right) → API Tokens
#   2. Click "Create Token" → "Create Custom Token"
#   3. Name it e.g. "Marketing Plugin"
#   4. Add these permissions (all Account scope):
#      - Cloudflare Pages → Edit
#      - Workers R2 Storage → Edit
#      - Access: Organizations, Identity Providers, and Groups → Edit
#      - Workers Scripts → Edit
#      - Stream → Edit
#      - Access: Apps and Policies → Edit
#   5. Click "Continue to summary" → "Create Token"
#
# How to find your Account ID:
#   1. Go to dash.cloudflare.com
#   2. Click on any domain (or go to Workers & Pages)
#   3. Your Account ID is in the right sidebar under "Account ID"
#
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# ─── Higgsfield MCP (Image + Video Generation) ───────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Generates AI ad images (Nano Banana, Soul) and videos (Kling 3.0,
#               Veo 3.1, Seedance 2.0) with UGC presets, talking heads, and
#               character training for multi-ad-set consistency.
#
# No API key needed — Higgsfield uses platform-level MCP authentication.
# Add the Higgsfield MCP to your Claude Code settings:
#
#   "mcpServers": {
#     "higgsfield": { "url": "https://mcp.higgsfield.ai" }
#   }
#
# Then connect your Higgsfield account through the OAuth prompt.

# ─── fal-ai MCP (Music + Transcription) ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Generates background music (ACE-Step) and transcribes UGC
#               video audio (Whisper). Available as a platform-level MCP tool
#               (mcp__fal-ai__*) — no API key configuration needed.

# ─── Apify (Competitor Intelligence) ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Scrapes Meta Ad Library to find competitor ads, download their
#               creatives, and analyse what's working in your market.
# OPTIONAL — only needed for competitor research features.
#
# How to get your API token:
#   1. Sign up at apify.com
#   2. Go to console.apify.com/account/integrations
#   3. Copy your Personal API Token
#   Free tier: ~50 scrape runs/month (enough for weekly competitor scans)
#
APIFY_API_TOKEN=

# ─── Google Analytics 4 (Optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Tracks landing page visitors and conversions.
# OPTIONAL — the plugin runs without it, but you won't have conversion data.
#
# Setup requires two steps:
#   A) Service account JSON key (file placed in plugin root)
#   B) GA4 Property IDs (numeric IDs from your GA4 account)
#
# How to get the service account key:
#   1. Go to console.cloud.google.com → Create/select a project
#   2. Enable "Google Analytics Data API" (APIs & Services → Library)
#   3. IAM & Admin → Service Accounts → Create Service Account
#      Name: "marketing-plugin" — no special GCP roles needed
#   4. Click the service account → Keys tab → Add Key → JSON → Download
#   5. Rename the file to ga4-service-account.json
#   6. Place it in the apg-marketing-plugin/ folder
#   7. Go to analytics.google.com → Admin → Property Access Management
#   8. Add service account email as Viewer (email is in the JSON under "client_email")
#
# How to find your GA4 Property ID:
#   Google Analytics → Admin (gear icon) → Property Settings → Property ID
#   It's a numeric value like 123456789
#
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS points to the JSON key file
# GA4_PROPERTY_ID is for your landing page domain (e.g. go.yourdomain.com)
# GA4_PROPERTY_ID_HOME is for your main website — optional, can be left blank
#
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=ga4-service-account.json
GA4_PROPERTY_ID=
GA4_PROPERTY_ID_HOME=

# ─── Anthropic API (Competitor Analysis) ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Powers scripts/analyse-competitor-creatives.py — sends competitor
#               ad images/video frames to Claude for 65-field creative analysis.
# OPTIONAL — only needed if you run competitor creative analysis.
#
# How to get your API key:
#   1. Go to console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#   2. Create a new key named e.g. "marketing-plugin"
#   Note: If Claude Code is already set up in your environment, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#         may already be set globally — run `echo $ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` to check.
#
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─── fal.ai (Video Transcription) ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does: Powers scripts/transcribe-ugc.py — transcribes real filmed UGC
#               footage via fal.ai Whisper for caption generation.
# OPTIONAL — only needed if you transcribe real filmed footage.
#             AI-generated UGC (Higgsfield) uses scenes.json dialogue directly.
#             All other fal.ai operations use the platform-level fal-ai MCP (no key needed).
#
# How to get your API key:
#   1. Sign up at fal.ai
#   2. Go to fal.ai/dashboard/keys
#   3. Create a new key
#   Cost: ~$0.006/minute of audio (~$0.001 for an 8s clip)
#
FAL_API_KEY=
